 Bids can be faked to gain advantage over others.

documentation.text:
Place a blinded bid with
 `blindedBid` = keccak256(abi.encodePacked(value, fake, secret)).
 The sent ether is only refunded if the bid is correctly revealed in the
 revealing phase. The bid is valid if the ether sent together with the bid
 is at least "value" and "fake" is not true. Setting "fake" to true and
 sending not the exact amount are ways to hide the real bid but still
 make the required deposit. The same address can make multiple bids.

params.beneficiaryAddress: receives the highest bid after the bidding ends.
params.revealTime: period in seconds after the bidding ended

params.fakes: list of flags in the same order indicating the real or fake bids when bid was added.
params.secrets: list of secrets attached in the same order when the bid was added.
params.values: list of bid amount in the same order when bid was added.

TooEarly(uint256).notice: Called too early. Try later at `time`.

bid(bytes32).notice: Place a blinded bid with `blindedBid` = keccak256(abi.encodePacked(value, fake, secret)). The sent ether is only refunded if the bid is correctly revealed in the revealing phase. The bid is valid if the ether sent together with the bid is at least "value" and "fake" is not true. Setting "fake" to true and sending not the exact amount are ways to hide the real bid but still make the required deposit. The same address can make multiple bids.

reveal(uint256[],bool[],bytes32[]).notice: Reveal your bids. You will get a refund for all correctly blinded invalid bids and for all bids except for the totally highest.
